<br>
We get criticized for NOT awarding loot to members.<br>
We get criticized FOR awarding loot to members.<br>
<br>
We get criticized for KEEPING people that some of you don't like.<br>
We get criticized for NOT keeping people that some of you don't like.<br>
<br>
Why any of this should matter to people who are no longer part of the guild or who did not think it important to work together on their grievances is beyond me.<br>
<br>
A well-prepared and well-balanced critique is the best thing a guild (or a person) can hope to learn from.  Believe it or not, we strive on a daily basis to look for constructive feedback on how to make things better.  I'm sure other guilds do the exact same thing.  Contradictory messages and rants do NOT a balanced critique make.<br>
<br>
If you wish to rant because you were not as well-equipped as the main tank and that others received loot you could have used before you did, feel free to.  This is RANTS and FLAMES, after all.  <br>
<br>
